text: As a police officer & homicide detective, I saw the horrifying effects of gun violence in our country. These are images & moments that I can never forget. I mourn for the victims of the #ParklandShooting & for the survivors who'll forever carry the scars of this tragedy.

The safety and security of our children should be our nation’s first and foremost priority. They should not feel threatened or afraid in the classroom. As we await answers from Parkland, Florida, I ask you to keep these young Americans and their families in your prayers.

Saturday’s Grand Canyon helicopter accident is a tragic loss of life. My heart goes out the victims and their families. The National Transportation Safety Board has opened an investigation to prevent a tragedy like this from happening in the future. #AZ01
Watching the news from Virginia. I am keeping my Republican colleagues and those in the truck in my prayers.
What do you hope to hear @realDonaldTrump discuss in tonight's #StateOfTheUnion? Reply with your "Other" responses. #AZ01 #SOTU

Today, and every day, we remember and honor the victims and survivors of the Holocaust. We must stand against anti-semitism, and we must ensure this is something that will never happen again.  

#InternationalHolocaustRemembranceDay
The state of Arizona and the National Park Service will be providing the resources necessary to keep the Grand Canyon open during the government shutdown. #AZ01
The strength of our nation and the very idea of the American Dream are rooted in the longstanding notion that we are a country built by immigrants seeking a new life.
I will be on @KTAR923 in 10 minutes. Tune in to hear about my priorities for 2018, and the work we are doing for Arizona. #AZ01

The House of Representatives had to vote on the tax bill again, because Congressional leaders have rushed the entire tax reform process. This process should have been more transparent and comprehensive to ensure that this reform plan brings relief for families.
#HanukkahSameach to all celebrating the Festival of Lights! #AZ01

Two months ago, I signed onto the Bring Jobs Home Act. This commonsense legislation incentivizes companies to bring jobs back to the U.S. and keep them here. I am proud to support legislation that will create jobs for #AZ01 families.

As we learn more about how the tax bill will impact Americans, it's clear that it'll hurt hardworking, middle-class families, raise taxes on entrepreneurs, & give massive tax cuts to the wealthiest & multinational corporations. The American people deserve better. #AZ01
What is the best cookie? #NationalCookieDay

As of this morning, our office has received letters, emails, and calls from 1,205 constituents in #AZ01 on the tax reform proposal – 133 in support of H.R. 1 and 1,072 in opposition. #TaxReform
What is your favorite sandwich? #NationalSandwichDay
My thoughts and prayers are with the victims of the attack in Manhattan and their loved ones.
I'll be on the House Floor soon to talk about Congress' inaction on funding the Children's Health Insurance Program. Tune into @CSPAN! #AZ01
Last night's attack against innocent concert goers is heartbreaking. Pat and I are praying for the victims of this senseless, evil shooting.
It takes 21 months for wages of American Indian & Alaska Native women to match those of non-Native men in 2016. #NativeWomenEqualPay
L'Shanah Tovah to all celebrating #RoshHashanah. Pat and I wish you a happy and healthy new year! #AZ01
This #HispanicHeritageMonth we reflect on the achievements of Latinos in our communities & contributions they have made to our society.
Arizona is praying for everyone in FL. Please stay safe and follow the instruction of emergency personnel. #HurricaneIrma #AZ01
I'll be at North Star Business Center in Show Low from 2-3 today. Stop by to meet me and my staff! #TomInYourTown
#DACA improved the lives of thousands of young Arizonans & grown our economy. I urge @potus to protect it & provide stability to #DREAMers.
Please continue to think of and pray for those struggling with the aftermath of Hurricane Harvey.

Today is the 5th anniversary of #DACA, which has boosted and strengthened local economies across Arizona and the country.

.@realDonaldTrump: You—not your staff or family—need to immediately and specifically condemn the actions of white supremacists...
Violence & hate speech have no place in our communities. We must stand together against hatred & disrespect on display in Charlottesville.
The brave men and women who wish to serve and defend our nation in the military should be allowed to do so.
Sen. McCain has dedicated his life to serving our nation with honor. Tonight we keep him and his family in our thoughts and prayers.

Arizonans I have spoken with are stressed and anxious as they watch politicians in Washington threaten to take away their health coverage.
The news of Donald Trump Jr.’s meeting with a Kremlin-linked lawyer is deeply troubling. This is about putting country above politics.
We must get serious about protecting our country against cyber attacks that could impact our elections and undermine our democracy.
I will keep fighting for greater #transparency of presidential travel costs. The American taxpayers deserve no less. #FY18NDAA
The 1st of my 3 amendments to #FY18NDAA passed. It requires DoD to brief the Armed Services Cmte on unused/excess ag equipment for disposal.
If we want to get serious about fixing our #healthcare system & bringing down costs, we must work together on bipartisan legislation. (9/9)
While we play partisan games, the health and wellbeing of our families, friends, and neighbors is at risk. #SenateHealthCareBill
From the beginning, these pieces of legislation have been crafted behind closed doors w/o input from doctors, nurses & #healthcare leaders.
Meaning hundreds of thousands of people, including nursing home patients, who rely on life-saving coverage will be kicked off #Medicaid.
Recent reports show the cost of #Medicaid cuts in this bill could cost #Arizona more than $7 billion.
The cost of this legislation will be paid by those who can least afford it.
We're placing our working families, our elderly, veterans, & Native Americans in harm’s way by making coverage unaffordable & unattainable.
This bill, like the #AHCA, proposes drastic cuts to #Medicaid and would saddle my constituents with skyrocketing premiums and deductibles.
Mr. Speaker, I rise today to express my deep misgivings about the recent #healthcare proposal put forth in the #Senate.
The #FinsburyPark attack is tragic. No one should be targeted for their religion or beliefs. Our thoughts & prayers are with London today.
Happy #FathersDay to all the role models, heroes, and fathers out there! I hope you have a wonderful day spent with loved ones and family.
This morning's attack on my colleagues, their staff, & Capitol police during practice for Thursday's @thehillbaseball game is heartbreaking.
My thoughts & prayers are with the victims of the #LondonAttacks. We must stand with our international partners to defeat terror everywhere.
This morning I'll be speaking on the @HouseFloor, urging my colleagues to support my amendment that provides resources to victims of abuse.

#HappyEaster to all who are celebrating with loved ones today.

On #EqualPayDay, and every day, we are reminded of the work left to do. I'm committed to closing the pay gap and bringing equality to #AZ01.
We will always stand with our allies against terrorism. My heart goes out to the victims and survivors of the attack in London.
Thank you @girlscouts for your work to build girls of courage, confidence, and character for over a century. Happy 105th birthday! #AZ01

I stand ready to work across the aisle to pass legislation that moves our country forward. It's time to act for hardworking AZ families.
